data.sampled: The best multiple choice answer to this question is option a) Heap Sort. Heap sort is an improvement to the binary tree sort and it is based on the idea of organizing the data in a binary tree-like structure called a heap, where the root element is always the minimum element. Unlike binary tree sort, the heap sort is based on insertions and deletions from the heap to ensure that the heap remains ordered by size. It has a time complexity of O(n log n) in the worst case, and O(n log n) on average, making it a faster sorting algorithm compared to others such as the binary tree sort.
